article.description: South Florida defeated host Boston College, 82-65, Wednesday night in the semifinals of the WNIT.
article.headline: Stokes scores 22 to lead South Florida to WNIT title game
article.linkText: South Florida tops BC to reach WNIT title game
article.story:
CHESTNUT HILL, Mass. -- South Florida defeated host Boston College, 82-65, Wednesday night in the semifinals of the WNIT.

The win was the fourth straight for the Bulls and their eighth victory in the past nine games. USF (26-10) advances to the championship game against Kansas at 2 p.m. on Saturday.

USF took control by holding the Eagles without a field goal for just under six minutes in the second half. During that stretch, the Bulls got 13 points from Jasmine Wynne and two 3-pointers from Janea Stokes.

Boston College never got closer than 11 points in the final six minutes.

Stokes finished 22 points on 7-of-16 shooting from the field, 5-for-9 from behind the arc. Wynne added 19 points.

USF also forced Boston College into 15 turnovers which led to 25 points, while committing five including two in the second half.
